definitions.definition: An island and traditional county at the northwestern extremity of north Wales . It is separated from Caernarfonshire on the mainland by a narrow stretch of water called the Menai Strait . The county was merged into Gwynedd in 1974.
A unitary authority in Wales , Isle of Anglesey County Council , created in 1996 when it was separated from Gwynedd.
A marquisate in the peerage of the United Kingdom .
